                {
                    "name": "Luring Cry",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "text": "60 feet; <b>Requirements</b> The leucrotta's last action was Sound Mimicry; <b>Effect</b> The leucrotta utters a plaintive cry to draw its prey closer. Each creature within the emanation that was deceived by Sound Mimicry must succeed at a DC 19 Will save or become <b>fascinated</b> and compelled to move toward the sound of the leucrotta's voice on their turn. Fascinated creatures are also <b>flat-footed</b>. If the leucrotta attacks, the fascinated condition ends only for the creature that is attacked. If the leucrotta speaks a creature's name while using its Luring Cry, that creature takes a \u20132 circumstance penalty to their saving throw to resist the ability. On a successful save, a creature is temporarily immune to Luring Cry for 24 hours.",
